1
00:00:35,302 --> 00:00:38,338
<i>I, Mordecai.</i>

2
00:00:38,472 --> 00:00:41,976
<i>Everyone has their story.</i>

3
00:00:42,109 --> 00:00:46,514
<i>I was born</i>
<i>July 27th, 1933,</i>

4
00:00:46,648 --> 00:00:49,751
<i>in Janów Podlaski, Poland.</i>

5
00:00:49,884 --> 00:00:51,786
<i>My father tells me</i>

6
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:54,421
<i>it was a very hot day.</i>

7
00:00:58,358 --> 00:01:00,828
Yohanan!

8
00:01:12,406 --> 00:01:15,710
Mordecai!

9
00:01:33,995 --> 00:01:37,164
Jakub! Jakub!

10
00:01:45,907 --> 00:01:47,775
Ssh!

11
00:02:44,331 --> 00:02:46,466
Oh, boy.

12
00:03:06,821 --> 00:03:08,756
What now?

13
00:03:11,458 --> 00:03:13,393
- What?
<i>- Hey, Dad.</i>

14
00:03:13,528 --> 00:03:15,863
- Yeah, hello-- Marvin?
- <i>Yeah.</i>

15
00:03:15,997 --> 00:03:18,398
What? I can't hear
what you're saying.

16
00:03:18,533 --> 00:03:20,400
I can't take it anymore.
I'm picking you up.

17
00:03:20,535 --> 00:03:22,269
We're getting you
a new phone.

18
00:03:22,402 --> 00:03:24,939
<i>No, don't come.</i>
<i>I'm busy now.</i>

19
00:03:25,073 --> 00:03:27,041
I'm on my way, Dad.

20
00:03:27,942 --> 00:03:31,478
Look, Ryan, the cigars need
more time to age.

21
00:03:31,612 --> 00:03:34,015
<i>Marvin,</i>
<i>you're running out of cash.</i>

22
00:03:34,148 --> 00:03:36,316
<i>You can't hold out forever.</i>

23
00:03:36,450 --> 00:03:38,586
Okay, I gotta go,
I'll see you later.

24
00:03:50,832 --> 00:03:53,000
Mrs. Gomez!

25
00:03:53,134 --> 00:03:55,302
Mrs. Gomez! <i>Qué paso?</i>

26
00:03:55,435 --> 00:03:56,671
<i>"Qué pasó?"</i>
<i>Qué tú piensas?</i>

27
00:03:56,804 --> 00:03:58,806
It's your crazy father again.

28
00:04:00,942 --> 00:04:02,476
Mom! What's going on?

29
00:04:02,610 --> 00:04:05,646
- Go ask him.
- Dad!

30
00:04:15,422 --> 00:04:17,658
What the fuck?!

31
00:04:22,730 --> 00:04:24,866
Dad! Dad!

32
00:04:26,934 --> 00:04:28,603
What for you sneak up
on me like that?

33
00:04:28,736 --> 00:04:30,138
What the hell are you doing?

34
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:31,539
Your mother,
she can't step into

35
00:04:31,672 --> 00:04:33,406
the tub to take shower,

36
00:04:33,541 --> 00:04:35,342
so we make walk-in shower.

37
00:04:35,475 --> 00:04:37,779
Yeah-- so you have
a jackhammer?!

38
00:04:37,912 --> 00:04:41,249
Well, this place is
built like bunker, all cement.

39
00:04:41,381 --> 00:04:43,450
What you want me to use,
hammer and chisel?

40
00:04:43,584 --> 00:04:44,852
- Maybe a toothpick?
- No, I want you

41
00:04:44,986 --> 00:04:47,054
- to call a plumber.
- I am a plumber!

42
00:04:47,188 --> 00:04:48,790
You retired 15 years ago.

43
00:04:48,923 --> 00:04:50,625
How are you and Mom
supposed to wash

44
00:04:50,758 --> 00:04:52,160
while you build this thing?

45
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:53,995
Mrs. Gomez, nice lady,

46
00:04:54,128 --> 00:04:56,063
we use her bathroom.

47
00:05:37,305 --> 00:05:39,106
Mom!

48
00:05:43,611 --> 00:05:46,280
Mom!

49
00:05:46,413 --> 00:05:49,951
What is your yelling
at your mother?!

50
00:05:50,084 --> 00:05:52,086
- I raised you!
- I know, but he's--

51
00:05:52,220 --> 00:05:54,889
--and I almost died
giving birth to you.

52
00:05:55,022 --> 00:05:56,624
You have huge head.

53
00:05:56,757 --> 00:05:58,659
I know.
All I wanted to do

54
00:05:58,793 --> 00:06:00,427
was come here,
take him to the mall,

55
00:06:00,561 --> 00:06:01,729
and buy him a new phone.

56
00:06:01,863 --> 00:06:03,664
That's it.
This is what I get.

57
00:06:03,798 --> 00:06:06,067
Okay, I go with you.

58
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:07,802
Well, he's on a mission
in there right now,

59
00:06:07,935 --> 00:06:09,503
I don't think he's gonna
really listen to you.

60
00:06:09,637 --> 00:06:10,838
We'll see about that.

61
00:06:10,972 --> 00:06:13,140
Mordecai,
we're going to the mall,

62
00:06:13,274 --> 00:06:15,375
or no hanky-panky.

63
00:06:16,177 --> 00:06:18,546
Okay, go get ready.

64
00:06:20,781 --> 00:06:23,383
Okay, we get ready.

65
00:06:26,621 --> 00:06:28,455
Okay, we get ready.

66
00:06:28,589 --> 00:06:30,258
Yeah, but I could--
I could fix this.

67
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:31,626
I could put some more...

68
00:06:31,759 --> 00:06:33,094
- Dad.
- ...electrical tape on it.

69
00:06:33,227 --> 00:06:34,662
- That's what I'll do.
- Dad, face facts.

70
00:06:34,795 --> 00:06:36,364
The phone is dead.

71
00:06:36,496 --> 00:06:39,399
You should bury
the Jeep with that phone.

72
00:06:41,002 --> 00:06:42,770
- "Ha-ha."
- How about that other Jeep?

73
00:06:42,904 --> 00:06:44,939
That Nazi shit car
of yours, huh?

74
00:06:45,072 --> 00:06:46,741
Going to rain, Mordecai.

75
00:06:46,874 --> 00:06:48,542
What rain?
Where's the rain?

76
00:06:56,284 --> 00:06:57,785
Ugh!

77
00:06:57,919 --> 00:07:00,521
Great-- Dad, I thought
you were gonna get a new window.

78
00:07:00,655 --> 00:07:02,590
Who needs new window? Here.

79
00:07:02,723 --> 00:07:04,825
Perhaps when the--
the big cigar deal

80
00:07:04,959 --> 00:07:06,661
actually happens,
then I get the window,

81
00:07:06,794 --> 00:07:08,529
- and maybe new car with it.
- All right, we're not

82
00:07:08,663 --> 00:07:09,997
having this conversation
right now.

83
00:07:10,131 --> 00:07:12,533
I ask for the...
report on the... loan.

84
00:07:12,667 --> 00:07:14,969
There's water
on floor back here.

85
00:07:15,102 --> 00:07:17,772
Talk about being big shot
in the cigar business, huh,

86
00:07:17,905 --> 00:07:19,774
now here in the making,
and you say nothing.

87
00:07:19,907 --> 00:07:22,442
- Please, please.
- Nothing, not even an update.

88
00:07:22,576 --> 00:07:24,145
Fine, you want an update?
Next week, we get

89
00:07:24,278 --> 00:07:25,913
a new batch of samples,
then we'll know.

90
00:07:26,047 --> 00:07:27,915
- It's not plumbing.
- Water on the floor--

91
00:07:28,049 --> 00:07:29,550
Look what happened
in all my life.

92
00:07:29,684 --> 00:07:30,851
Huh? Look what I do for him,

93
00:07:30,985 --> 00:07:32,520
after he's shown
no respect for me.

94
00:07:32,653 --> 00:07:34,288
- My-- My own son!
- "Respect."

95
00:07:34,422 --> 00:07:36,691
- Where's my update?
- Enough with the two of you.

96
00:07:36,824 --> 00:07:39,492
Car floor is full of water.

97
00:07:39,627 --> 00:07:42,029
Marvin, pull the plug.

98
00:07:42,163 --> 00:07:44,565
- I'm drowning back here.
- Oh, my God.

99
00:07:50,237 --> 00:07:53,473
Brighten up,
this is light here, we go now.

100
00:07:57,745 --> 00:08:01,015
I get my war reparations
check from Germany,

101
00:08:01,148 --> 00:08:02,416
I go buy brassiere.

102
00:08:02,550 --> 00:08:04,051
How come you get
reparations check,

103
00:08:04,185 --> 00:08:05,286
and I get shit?

104
00:08:05,419 --> 00:08:06,787
Because I suffered

105
00:08:06,921 --> 00:08:08,923
more than you,
that's mine.

106
00:08:09,056 --> 00:08:12,059
How many times
I have to say it?

107
00:08:12,193 --> 00:08:14,128
What is she talkin'...

108
00:08:19,633 --> 00:08:21,035
Ahh.

109
00:08:21,168 --> 00:08:22,636
- What do you think?
- No-no-no, this is not--

110
00:08:22,770 --> 00:08:24,205
- Pretty cool, right?
- Not for me.

111
00:08:24,338 --> 00:08:26,007
It's all right, come on,
you're gonna be all right.

112
00:08:26,140 --> 00:08:27,608
- We got the phone right here.
- Marvin, Marvin--

113
00:08:27,742 --> 00:08:29,043
I don't know
how to use iPhone.

114
00:08:29,176 --> 00:08:30,911
- I got landline.
- If you don't like it,

115
00:08:31,045 --> 00:08:32,513
you wanna give it back,
we'll get another one.

116
00:08:32,646 --> 00:08:33,848
- No--
- Yeah, but I want you

117
00:08:33,981 --> 00:08:35,316
- to look at this, look.
- No.

118
00:08:35,449 --> 00:08:36,884
Come on.
All right.

119
00:08:37,018 --> 00:08:38,686
I'm gonna go get some help.
Don't go anywhere.

120
00:08:38,819 --> 00:08:40,321
I don't...

121
00:08:40,454 --> 00:08:42,156
Marv...

122
00:08:44,759 --> 00:08:47,695
That's going to allow us
to add some depth to our image,

123
00:08:47,828 --> 00:08:50,664
like this... see?

124
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:12,420
See, in a digital world,
we create our own reality.

125
00:09:12,553 --> 00:09:15,923
And through technology,
we create anything we want to.

126
00:09:16,057 --> 00:09:18,659
We can make it real,
make it come to life.

127
00:09:18,793 --> 00:09:21,062
Just something that existed
in our minds today

128
00:09:21,195 --> 00:09:24,865
is now being shared
with the world, instantly.

129
00:09:27,034 --> 00:09:29,136
And here is
a perfect opportunity

130
00:09:29,270 --> 00:09:31,705
for me to show you exactly
what I was talking about.

131
00:09:31,839 --> 00:09:33,574
Oh!

132
00:09:33,707 --> 00:09:36,143
Oh, my!

133
00:09:37,878 --> 00:09:40,014
That is all I have

134
00:09:40,147 --> 00:09:42,183
for all of you today.
Thank you so much for coming,

135
00:09:42,316 --> 00:09:44,351
and I hope to see you
next time.

136
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:47,822
Hey, there.
Are you interested

137
00:09:47,955 --> 00:09:50,024
in a course in digital art?

138
00:09:50,157 --> 00:09:52,460
Digital art?

139
00:09:52,593 --> 00:09:54,395
Thought this was phone store.

140
00:09:54,529 --> 00:09:55,896
Yeah...

141
00:09:56,030 --> 00:09:57,998
I don't even know
what I'm doing here.

142
00:09:58,132 --> 00:09:59,534
Sorry.

143
00:09:59,667 --> 00:10:01,202
- Wanna know a secret?
- Yeah.

144
00:10:01,335 --> 00:10:03,904
- Sometimes I don't either.
- Yeah.

145
00:10:04,038 --> 00:10:06,508
- I'm Nina, by the way.
- Nina.

146
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:08,876
My son, he wants me
to use an iPhone.

147
00:10:09,009 --> 00:10:12,613
But I happy with my old
flippy phone for calling.

148
00:10:12,746 --> 00:10:14,682
It's been with me

149
00:10:14,815 --> 00:10:16,484
through all my plumbing years.

150
00:10:16,617 --> 00:10:18,018
Are you having trouble

151
00:10:18,152 --> 00:10:19,820
hearing who you're
talking to on that thing?

152
00:10:19,954 --> 00:10:21,355
I have trouble
hearing, period.

153
00:10:21,489 --> 00:10:24,024
Dad, there you are,
don't wander off, please.

154
00:10:24,158 --> 00:10:25,693
Come here, I want you
to meet somebody.

155
00:10:25,826 --> 00:10:28,863
This is Jared,
he's an iPhone specialist.

156
00:10:28,996 --> 00:10:30,532
Pleased to make
your acquaintance, sir.

157
00:10:30,664 --> 00:10:31,966
What's up, Nina?

158
00:10:32,099 --> 00:10:34,603
Oh, hi, uh,
are you already together?

159
00:10:34,735 --> 00:10:37,671
Oh, not in a retail
sort of sense.

160
00:10:37,805 --> 00:10:40,674
I actually have another class
I have to get to anyway, so--

161
00:10:40,808 --> 00:10:43,077
but good luck
with your phone.

162
00:10:43,210 --> 00:10:45,679
Mr. Samel, I present to you
the state-of-the-art

163
00:10:45,813 --> 00:10:47,616
of the state-of-the-art,
the new iPhone.

164
00:10:47,748 --> 00:10:49,884
So what cost this phone

165
00:10:50,017 --> 00:10:51,752
- with no buttons?
- Dad, you see

166
00:10:51,886 --> 00:10:53,555
these kids in the blue shirts--
you know what they call them?

167
00:10:53,687 --> 00:10:54,989
- What?
- Prodigies.

168
00:10:55,122 --> 00:10:56,824
- Because they're so smart.
- Oh, boy.

169
00:10:56,957 --> 00:10:59,326
Him? He don't look
like Einstein to me.

170
00:10:59,460 --> 00:11:01,563
- Dad, don't be rude, please.
- Rude? Why don't you show

171
00:11:01,695 --> 00:11:03,063
some respect yourself, huh?

172
00:11:03,197 --> 00:11:04,865
I don't want to come here
in the first place.

173
00:11:04,999 --> 00:11:07,401
I get the fuck out of here.

174
00:11:09,436 --> 00:11:11,438
Your card, Mr. Samel.

175
00:11:11,573 --> 00:11:13,908
<i>No bueno.</i>

176
00:11:15,176 --> 00:11:19,180
Should've gone
straight home. Here.

177
00:11:47,474 --> 00:11:49,243
Netta? Hon?

178
00:11:49,376 --> 00:11:50,811
Hi, I think she has

179
00:11:50,945 --> 00:11:52,746
a "welcome home" present
for you in there.

180
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:54,748
Let me take a quick sniff.

181
00:11:54,882 --> 00:11:57,051
Oh, boy. How was it
with your family?

182
00:11:57,184 --> 00:11:59,386
Don't even ask.
I get to the apartment,

183
00:11:59,521 --> 00:12:02,256
and there is smoke
billowing out of the door.

184
00:12:02,389 --> 00:12:04,225
- Smoke?
- Right, sorry, not smoke,

185
00:12:04,358 --> 00:12:06,760
it was plaster dust,
to be more specific.

186
00:12:06,894 --> 00:12:09,096
And a lot of it.
Everywhere.

187
00:12:09,230 --> 00:12:10,998
And that's just
the beginning of it.

188
00:12:11,131 --> 00:12:12,601
Then he's dragging me there...

189
00:12:15,402 --> 00:12:18,005
And then he's like this--

190
00:12:19,273 --> 00:12:22,176
"Hello? Hello? How are ya?"

191
00:12:24,144 --> 00:12:25,746
"Hello?
Can ya get me up there."

192
00:12:25,879 --> 00:12:27,248
Look at your dad.
Look at your dad.

193
00:12:27,381 --> 00:12:28,849
He screams at me
inside of the store

194
00:12:28,983 --> 00:12:30,619
and storms out.

195
00:12:30,751 --> 00:12:32,319
But you still love him.

196
00:12:32,453 --> 00:12:34,188
I'm just concerned

197
00:12:34,321 --> 00:12:37,191
that he's gonna continue
to get himself into trouble.

198
00:12:37,324 --> 00:12:39,493
You should just
move them in here.

199
00:12:40,327 --> 00:12:42,229
What part of
"jackhammering the bathtub"

200
00:12:42,363 --> 00:12:44,231
- didn't you understand?
- You don't know.

201
00:12:44,365 --> 00:12:47,101
He might do a really good job
on the bathroom.

202
00:12:47,234 --> 00:12:49,303
You know what?
If he wants to be included

203
00:12:49,436 --> 00:12:52,139
in your big deal,
include him.

204
00:12:52,906 --> 00:12:54,475
I'm getting the hang of this.

205
00:12:58,779 --> 00:13:00,749
You are a horrible father.

206
00:13:00,881 --> 00:13:03,384
It runs in the family.

207
00:13:06,053 --> 00:13:08,088
I'll do it right,
I'll get it right.

208
00:13:11,125 --> 00:13:13,060
Here you go, Mr. Schwartz.

209
00:13:15,396 --> 00:13:17,398
Well, that's it for now.

210
00:13:17,532 --> 00:13:20,134
See you next month
at the Survivors' Meeting,

211
00:13:20,267 --> 00:13:24,071
where we will celebrate
Ida Brown's 100th birthday.

212
00:13:24,204 --> 00:13:27,841
From Auschwitz to Aventura.

213
00:13:27,975 --> 00:13:29,943
Happy Birthday, Ida.

214
00:13:35,082 --> 00:13:38,052
This party is going
to be so amazing.

215
00:13:38,185 --> 00:13:39,820
How does it feel
to be almost 100

216
00:13:39,953 --> 00:13:41,889
with everything
that you've been through?

217
00:13:42,022 --> 00:13:44,825
Ah, I was
just about your age

218
00:13:44,958 --> 00:13:47,094
when I went into the camps.

219
00:13:47,227 --> 00:13:48,962
But I chose
not to let that

220
00:13:49,096 --> 00:13:51,566
define how I live my life.

221
00:13:51,700 --> 00:13:56,738
If I did, it would dishonor
my parents and my sister.

222
00:13:56,870 --> 00:13:58,573
Survivors have
to tell our stories

223
00:13:58,707 --> 00:14:02,544
to young people like you,
so it never happens again.

224
00:14:03,511 --> 00:14:05,279
<i>Good morning, Point East!</i>

225
00:14:05,412 --> 00:14:07,481
<i>The bus for</i>
<i>the bingo tournament is leaving</i>

226
00:14:07,615 --> 00:14:09,416
<i>in 15 minutes.</i>

227
00:14:09,551 --> 00:14:10,851
--even talking about?

228
00:14:10,984 --> 00:14:14,455
Why, hello,
Mr. and Mrs. Samel.

229
00:14:14,589 --> 00:14:17,091
Mr. Samel,
I was hoping to see you.

230
00:14:17,224 --> 00:14:20,027
I want you to enter
the bocce ball tournament

231
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:23,163
at our annual community
festival next month.

232
00:14:23,297 --> 00:14:26,668
Thank you, Mrs. Campbell,
but I no play bocce ball.

233
00:14:26,801 --> 00:14:30,471
Oh, but Mordecai,
it's going to be so much fun.

234
00:14:31,673 --> 00:14:34,408
You know, I was quite
an athlete when I was younger.

235
00:14:34,542 --> 00:14:38,379
Oh, I can tell.
So strong.

236
00:14:38,513 --> 00:14:40,682
Did you ever play
anything professionally?

237
00:14:40,815 --> 00:14:44,284
Enough of this nonsense,
I only going to tell this once.

238
00:14:44,418 --> 00:14:46,821
You stay away from my man.

239
00:14:46,954 --> 00:14:49,022
You buried
two husbands already.

240
00:14:49,156 --> 00:14:52,226
You're not stealing this one.
Mordecai, we go.

241
00:14:52,359 --> 00:14:53,862
I think that
bocce's not for me.

242
00:14:53,994 --> 00:14:55,896
Now listen to me,
you don't talk

243
00:14:56,029 --> 00:14:57,464
to that crazy shiksa.

244
00:14:57,599 --> 00:14:59,400
She was schtupping
Mr. Longstein.

245
00:14:59,534 --> 00:15:01,736
He tried from heart attack
on the spot.

246
00:15:01,870 --> 00:15:03,872
What are you--
meshuggeneh?

247
00:15:04,004 --> 00:15:05,540
We married 50 years.

248
00:15:05,673 --> 00:15:07,975
Every lady in the street,
