is on Thursday.

1500
01:30:03,537 --> 01:30:04,872
- so I come in--
- Dad.

1501
01:30:05,006 --> 01:30:06,774
No-no-no-no,
this is what I have to say.

1502
01:30:06,908 --> 01:30:08,709
I go to the bank
this morning.

1503
01:30:08,843 --> 01:30:10,578
Who knew the condo was
worth so much?

1504
01:30:10,711 --> 01:30:13,114
I take out a second mortgage.

1505
01:30:13,247 --> 01:30:14,849
For a rainy day.

1506
01:30:14,982 --> 01:30:17,685
Or for the unsuspecting jinx
of the cigar investment.

1507
01:30:17,818 --> 01:30:20,453
Also, it's possible

1508
01:30:20,588 --> 01:30:22,356
I'm proud of you.

1509
01:30:22,489 --> 01:30:24,424
It is a possibility.

1510
01:30:25,326 --> 01:30:27,128
Hm?

1511
01:30:32,667 --> 01:30:34,635
Hey, everybody, um...

1512
01:30:34,769 --> 01:30:36,570
I'd love to just take a second,
if you don't mind,

1513
01:30:36,704 --> 01:30:38,606
to introduce my father.

1514
01:30:38,739 --> 01:30:41,208
This is
Mordecai Samel.

1515
01:30:49,951 --> 01:30:53,087
Hey, are we gonna
get this done?

1516
01:30:55,623 --> 01:30:59,126
Actually,
I don't think we can.

1517
01:31:01,062 --> 01:31:04,298
How close are we to having
the best damn cigar of the year?

1518
01:31:04,432 --> 01:31:05,967
Oh, yeah-- very close.

1519
01:31:06,100 --> 01:31:08,336
Very close,
and once we have

1520
01:31:08,468 --> 01:31:10,538
the best damn cigar
of the year,

1521
01:31:10,671 --> 01:31:12,740
that's gonna cause
a lot of buzz, isn't it?

1522
01:31:12,873 --> 01:31:15,643
- Yeah, all that buzzing.
- Lot of buzzing.

1523
01:31:15,776 --> 01:31:17,511
I was under the impression

1524
01:31:17,645 --> 01:31:20,147
that you didn't have
the funds to wait it out.

1525
01:31:20,281 --> 01:31:22,249
Well, I think you were under
the wrong impression.

1526
01:31:22,383 --> 01:31:25,653
So, if you do wanna return
to the original deal structure,

1527
01:31:25,786 --> 01:31:28,756
we're gonna need to know
in the next 48 hours?

1528
01:31:28,889 --> 01:31:31,192
Yeah, no, 48 hours.

1529
01:31:37,932 --> 01:31:41,202
Mordecai, you got
so many calls on this thing.

1530
01:31:41,335 --> 01:31:44,038
You know, first crazy guy
from art gallery,

1531
01:31:44,171 --> 01:31:47,675
then Nina, then Jared,
who's coming here.

1532
01:31:47,808 --> 01:31:49,510
- What?
- Yeah.

1533
01:31:52,446 --> 01:31:55,082
You're gonna be a no-show
to your own exhibition?

1534
01:31:55,216 --> 01:31:58,185
No, I no leave Fela
alone at night.

1535
01:31:58,319 --> 01:32:00,721
- She don't want me to come.
- Then why are we here?

1536
01:32:00,855 --> 01:32:03,057
Why'd she tell us to come?

1537
01:32:03,190 --> 01:32:04,625
Fela?

1538
01:32:04,759 --> 01:32:07,328
Come on, get changed.

1539
01:32:07,461 --> 01:32:09,830
- You sure?
- Yeah, I sure.

1540
01:32:09,964 --> 01:32:11,866
You don't-- You don't--

1541
01:32:11,999 --> 01:32:13,467
- Ah.
- You want...

1542
01:32:43,798 --> 01:32:45,534
I come.

1543
01:32:45,666 --> 01:32:48,202
Yes, welcome.

1544
01:32:49,538 --> 01:32:51,806
This is my first art viewing.

1545
01:32:51,939 --> 01:32:55,009
Yeah, well, don't be nervous,
it's mine too.

1546
01:32:56,545 --> 01:32:59,680
Maybe we could meet
for lunch someday, huh?

1547
01:33:00,581 --> 01:33:02,249
Yes, okay.

1548
01:33:03,484 --> 01:33:05,886
I view your art now.

1549
01:33:06,921 --> 01:33:08,489
But my art is over here.

1550
01:33:08,622 --> 01:33:10,291
I know!

1551
01:33:27,875 --> 01:33:30,478
Fela, where's Mrs. Gomez?

1552
01:33:30,611 --> 01:33:32,547
How you get here?

1553
01:33:32,680 --> 01:33:34,181
What, you take phone taxi?

1554
01:33:34,315 --> 01:33:36,283
I... took a Marvin taxi.

1555
01:33:36,417 --> 01:33:38,587
I took a Netta taxi.

1556
01:33:38,719 --> 01:33:40,354
Marvin.

1557
01:33:40,488 --> 01:33:41,922
I'm glad you came.

1558
01:33:42,056 --> 01:33:44,625
I'm glad I came too, Dad.

1559
01:33:44,758 --> 01:33:46,794
Come here.

1560
01:33:48,896 --> 01:33:52,099
Dad, thank you
for everything you did for us.

1561
01:33:52,233 --> 01:33:54,068
It meant a lot.

1562
01:33:54,201 --> 01:33:56,437
Listen, I--
I wish to know about the deal,

1563
01:33:56,571 --> 01:33:59,574
but, um, with respect,
you don't have to say.

1564
01:33:59,707 --> 01:34:01,543
Dad, you should know
about the deal.

1565
01:34:01,675 --> 01:34:03,277
I gave them
two days to respond.

1566
01:34:03,410 --> 01:34:06,413
They responded in two hours!
I didn't get to the parking lot!

1567
01:34:06,548 --> 01:34:09,183
- You mean they buy?
- "They buy"? They buy big.

1568
01:34:09,316 --> 01:34:11,085
They buy big!

1569
01:34:11,218 --> 01:34:12,686
Mr. Mordecai!

1570
01:34:13,754 --> 01:34:15,055
- You ready?
- Huh?

1571
01:34:15,189 --> 01:34:17,224
- You ready?
- Oh, Nina, Jared.

1572
01:34:17,358 --> 01:34:19,660
I've never been
more happy in my life.

1573
01:34:25,833 --> 01:34:27,034
Ladies and gentlemen,

1574
01:34:27,168 --> 01:34:29,303
can I have
your attention please?

1575
01:34:33,340 --> 01:34:36,243
To the man
who has taught me...

1576
01:34:36,377 --> 01:34:38,245
so much.

1577
01:34:39,747 --> 01:34:41,448
I am so proud to present

1578
01:34:41,583 --> 01:34:44,785
Mordecai Samel's
Art History.

1579
01:34:44,919 --> 01:34:48,022
And Einsteins--
if you will, please.

1580
01:34:54,929 --> 01:34:57,131
Bravo.

1581
01:35:05,973 --> 01:35:07,942
Speech, Mordecai, speech!

1582
01:35:13,881 --> 01:35:16,383
You see?
We teach each other.

1583
01:35:16,518 --> 01:35:18,919
That's what friends do.

1584
01:35:31,398 --> 01:35:33,067
Well...

1585
01:35:33,200 --> 01:35:36,770
now, the first thing
I would like to say is that

1586
01:35:36,904 --> 01:35:40,441
I talk too much.

1587
01:35:40,575 --> 01:35:42,510
Then I, you know...

1588
01:35:42,644 --> 01:35:44,311
I look around.

1589
01:35:44,445 --> 01:35:45,879
And I see...

1590
01:35:46,013 --> 01:35:49,149
...it's nice to be young.

1591
01:35:50,685 --> 01:35:52,820
It's nice to be old.

1592
01:35:54,188 --> 01:35:57,559
It's nice to have phone
with no buttons.

1593
01:36:02,697 --> 01:36:04,733
Also, it's...

1594
01:36:04,865 --> 01:36:06,500
it's nice to have family.

1595
01:36:13,307 --> 01:36:15,175
It's nice to have friends.

1596
01:36:43,638 --> 01:36:46,073
Mama.

1597
01:36:53,247 --> 01:36:54,683
L'chaim!

1598
01:36:54,815 --> 01:36:57,418
L'chaim!

1599
01:37:03,558 --> 01:37:06,193
Wonderful! Well done!

1600
01:37:06,327 --> 01:37:09,897
You see what I told you?
It always works out.

1601
01:37:15,804 --> 01:37:19,173
Fela? Fela?

1602
01:37:27,682 --> 01:37:29,350
Fela?

1603
01:37:29,483 --> 01:37:31,485
Fela? Fela?

1604
01:37:32,886 --> 01:37:34,455
It's me.

1605
01:37:35,623 --> 01:37:37,559
It's your husband.

1606
01:37:38,859 --> 01:37:40,427
Mordecai.

1607
01:37:41,629 --> 01:37:43,397
Where are you going?

1608
01:37:51,673 --> 01:37:53,974
I don't know.

1609
01:37:55,409 --> 01:37:57,478
Okay.

1610
01:37:57,612 --> 01:37:59,480
I'll go with you.

1611
01:37:59,614 --> 01:38:01,181
Come, I go with you.

1612
01:38:01,315 --> 01:38:03,785
- You-You...
- Yeah.

1613
01:38:03,917 --> 01:38:05,787
Come on.

1614
01:38:05,919 --> 01:38:07,354
Thank you.

1615
01:38:09,923 --> 01:38:12,292
- Mordecai?
- Yeah?

1616
01:38:13,595 --> 01:38:16,163
Yeah, let's go home.

1617
01:38:16,296 --> 01:38:18,098
Me.

1618
01:40:46,146 --> 01:40:47,682
- Oh.
- Do it one more time.

1619
01:40:51,118 --> 01:40:52,520
- That's good.
- That's good.

1620
01:40:52,654 --> 01:40:54,956
You know what?
When I was your age,

1621
01:40:55,088 --> 01:40:56,390
I grow up...

1622
01:40:56,524 --> 01:40:58,993
you know what I was wearing?

1623
01:40:59,126 --> 01:41:00,995
Diaper...

1624
01:41:01,128 --> 01:41:03,965
from a sack of potatoes!

1625
01:41:04,097 --> 01:41:09,069
I was sleeping
in a hole on straw.

1626
01:41:09,202 --> 01:41:11,438
I didn't have a house.

1627
01:41:12,840 --> 01:41:15,309
I was always hungry.

1628
01:41:15,442 --> 01:41:17,377
I didn't have a mommy.

1629
01:41:17,512 --> 01:41:20,048
- No?
- No.

1630
01:41:20,180 --> 01:41:22,717
I don't believe in dreams,

1631
01:41:22,850 --> 01:41:26,453
but this is
like a dream come true.

1632
01:41:27,689 --> 01:41:30,490
I have two grandkids
from my son,

1633
01:41:30,625 --> 01:41:34,161
I have five grandchildren
from my daughter.

1634
01:41:35,462 --> 01:41:38,600
And... work out
very good for me.

1635
01:41:38,733 --> 01:41:41,101
That's the story,
my friend.

